# Claude Code Instructions - Babykrant Project

## 🎯 Project Overview
Baby newspaper generator that creates personalized birth announcements with AI-generated articles based on birth date data (weather, news, astrology, name meanings, etc.)

## 👥 Team Workflow
**IMPORTANT:** We work with two Claudes:
- **Claude Chat (claude.ai):** Strategy, planning, research, feature design, roadmap decisions
- **Claude Code (you!):** Implementation, code changes, testing, debugging, commits

**Your role:** Execute tasks defined by Claude Chat. When stuck or need decisions, ask the user to consult Claude Chat.

## 📁 Key Files & Structure
- `/app/wizard/page.tsx` - Main wizard (3 steps: basis, extra vragen, fotos)
- `/app/test-results/page.tsx` - Data display & testing page
- `/app/generate-articles/page.tsx` - AI article generation UI
- `/app/api/generate-article/route.ts` - Claude Haiku API integration
- `/lib/types.ts` - Data type definitions
- `/lib/articleTypes.ts` - Article generation types & config
- `/lib/version.ts` - Centralized version management

## 🔧 Git Workflow
**CRITICAL:** Always work directly on `main` branch
- ❌ NEVER create `claude/*` feature branches
- ✅ Pull latest from main before starting
- ✅ Commit directly to main
- ✅ Push immediately after committing
- Format: `feat: description` or `fix: description` or `refactor: description`

**If git blocks you:** Don't create workarounds. Tell the user to fix git config.

## 🚀 Deployment
- Main branch auto-deploys to Vercel production
- Always test locally on `http://localhost:3000/test-results` before pushing
- Check Vercel deployment logs after each push
- Live site: babykrant-claude.vercel.app

## 🔑 Environment Variables (in Vercel)
- `ANTHROPIC_API_KEY` - Claude 3.5 Haiku (current, primary)
- `GEMINI_API_KEY` - Gemini 2.5 Flash (backup, not actively used)

**Never hardcode API keys!** Always use `process.env.ANTHROPIC_API_KEY`

## 🤖 AI Article Generation (Current Implementation)
- **Model:** Claude 3.5 Haiku (`claude-3-5-haiku-20241022`)
- **Endpoint:** Anthropic Messages API (`https://api.anthropic.com/v1/messages`)
- **Rate limiting:** 50 requests/day, $1.00 budget cap (currently DISABLED for testing)
- **Max tokens:** 1000 per section (to prevent truncation)
- **Temperature:** 0.7 (balance between creative and consistent)
- **Pricing:** ~$0.04 per complete babykrant (8 articles)

## 📝 Code Standards
- TypeScript strict mode enabled
- All new files need version comment at top: `// @version X.X.X`
- Update version in `lib/version.ts` when making releases
- Dutch language in UI, English in code/comments
- Consistent formatting: 2 spaces, semicolons
- Always provide COMPLETE files, never use placeholders like "// rest remains the same"

## 🧪 Testing Workflow
1. User fills wizard at `/wizard` with test data
2. Check data collection at `/test-results`
3. Generate articles at `/generate-articles`
4. Review output quality
5. If issues: report to user → Claude Chat decides next steps

## 🎨 Article Sections (8 total)
1. **hoofdartikel** (~250 words) - Birth story, warm & personal
2. **sterrenbeeld** (~180 words) - Zodiac & Chinese year
3. **nieuws** (~140 words) - News on birth date
4. **weer** (~80 words) - Weather report
5. **cultuur** (~130 words) - Music & TV highlights
6. **naam_betekenis** (~150 words) - Name etymology
7. **beroemde_namen** (~100 words) - Famous namesakes
8. **geboren_op_dag** (~100 words) - Born on this day

**Tone-of-voice for all sections:**
- Warm but not overly sentimental
- Informative without being boring
- Balance between positive and realistic
- Dutch language, proper grammar
- No markdown formatting in output (no **, ##, etc.)

## 🚨 Common Issues & Solutions
- **Articles truncated:** Check `maxOutputTokens` in API route (should be 1000)
- **Rate limit errors:** Check Anthropic Console usage
- **Missing data:** Ensure all API calls in test-results completed
- **Build errors:** Run `npm run build` locally before pushing
- **API 404 errors:** Check model name is exact: `claude-3-5-haiku-20241022`
- **Empty responses:** Check API key in Vercel env vars

